# Workspace Information Hierarchy — Enterprise UX

Status: **ENTERPRISE APPROVED** · Priority: **CRITICAL**

## Principle

Every workspace exists primarily to **perform work**.

Information should **support** the work — never dominate it.

**Target:** ~80% Work Area · ~20% Information Area

## Layout contract

1. Keep page header compact.
2. Keep Business Journey Navigator as a single compact horizontal strip.
3. Do **not** permanently mount large readiness / KPI / advisory widgets above the primary work area.
4. Place Overall Readiness, Stage Readiness, KPI cards, detailed progress, and extended Chanakya advisory inside a collapsible **Transaction Insights** panel (collapsed by default; minimal height when closed).
5. Primary work surface (e.g. Lender Pipeline) sits immediately below compact chrome and occupies most of the viewport — users begin working without scrolling for information.

## Chanakya

Chanakya stays visible in **compact** mode (one-line Live strip). Detailed guidance only when the user expands Transaction Insights or opens Chanakya Guide.

## Across Catalyst One

Workspace First. Information Second.  
Never sacrifice operational workspace for dashboards or informational widgets.  
Dashboards support execution — they do not replace it.
